{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-5-20251101","id":"msg_01Nb4kxkC5hjZB8ixgJFzp5F","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017BTAd1Utnp7Cc3HQLGsmZY","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Analyze codebase for template removal","prompt":"Analyze what specs and code patterns are needed for this task.\n\nTask: 移除 src/templates/ 下的 .txt 模板文件，让 trellis init 直接从 Trellis 项目自身的实际文件（.trellis/ 目录下的 .md 和 .sh 文件）复制到目标项目。实现「吃自己的狗粮」模式。\n\n(Translation: Remove .txt template files under src/templates/, make `trellis init` copy directly from Trellis project's own actual files (.md and .sh files under .trellis/ directory) to the target project. Implement \"eat your own dog food\" mode.)\n\nDev Type: backend\n\nInstructions:\n1. Search .trellis/structure/ for relevant spec files\n2. Search the codebase for related modules and patterns - specifically:\n   - Find src/templates/ and understand the current template system\n   - Find the `init` command implementation\n   - Find what files are currently being copied/templated\n3. Identify files that should be added to jsonl context\n\nOutput format (use exactly this format):\n\n## implement.jsonl\n- path: <relative file path>, reason: <why needed>\n- path: <relative file path>, reason: <why needed>\n\n## check.jsonl\n- path: <relative file path>, reason: <why needed>\n\n## debug.jsonl\n- path: <relative file path>, reason: <why needed>\n\n## Suggested Scope\n<single word for commit scope, e.g., auth, api, ui>\n\n## Technical Notes\n<any important technical considerations for prd.md>","subagent_type":"research","model":"opus"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":294,"cache_read_input_tokens":31460,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":294,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"916adf87-2fe7-4a87-9c04-ba645fc5dabd",